body:
Ignore optimization when the unpacking operators are present  [[PEP - 448] ](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0448/)

Eg:
```
>>> a = [1,2,3] 
>>> b = [4,5,6]
>>> [*a]
[1,2,3]
>>> 6 in [*a, *b]
True
```
Thanks @scoder @da-woods for helping out with this contribution.


Fixes #3938

commit.message: Add the test case for starred expressions in `in` operator
ignore opti if there are one or more starred expressions
add the same test in a separate file for tracking purposes (as in the hacker's guidelines)
remove duplicate and rename based on issue id (3938)
